function setCookie( name, value, expires, path, domain, secure ) {
var today = new Date();
today.setTime( today.getTime() );
if ( expires ) {
expires = expires * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24;
}
var expires_date = new Date( today.getTime() + (expires) );
document.cookie = name+'='+escape( value ) +
( ( expires ) ? ';expires='+expires_date.toGMTString() : '' ) +
( ( path ) ? ';path=' + path : '' ) +
( ( domain ) ? ';domain=' + domain : '' ) +
( ( secure ) ? ';secure' : '' );
}
//----------------------------------------------------------
// check if cookie defined
//----------------------------------------------------------
function getCookie(name) {
var start = document.cookie.indexOf( name + "=" );
var len = start + name.length + 1;
if ( ( !start ) && ( name != document.cookie.substring( 0, name.length ) ) ) {
return null;
}
if ( start == -1 ) return null;
var end = document.cookie.indexOf( ';', len );
if ( end == -1 ) end = document.cookie.length;
return unescape( document.cookie.substring( len, end ) );
}
//------------------------------------------------------------
// Remove cookie
//------------------------------------------------------------
function removeCookie( name, path, domain) {
if ( getCookie( name ) )
{
document.cookie = name + '=' + ( ( path ) ? ';path=' + path : '') + ( ( domain ) ? ';domain=' + domain : '' ) + ';expires=Thu, 01-Jan-1970 00:00:01 GMT';
}
}

}
return domainname;
}

<p>
<strong>1:27pm</strong>: India huddle together. Oh hello! <strong>Miller comes out to open</strong> with QdK. This means that Amla has been pushed down. One slip in position. Bhuvneshwar comes round the stumps
</p>
<p>
Ashwin: "Umpires for this match??" - Dar and Shamshuddin.
</p>
<p>
<strong>1:15pm</strong>: Just a couple of pacers for India and <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/929859.html" target="_blank">Bhuvneshwar Kumar </a>has stressed that he has neither lost nor compromised on swing.
</p>
<p>
<strong>1pm</strong>: 'The captains walk out for the toss,' says Rachna. And a giant bunch of balloons make their way to the field. <strong>South Africa choose to bat</strong>.
</p>
<p>
<strong>AB de Villiers</strong>: 99% [the decision is because of the heat]. It looks really a good wicket. We will look to set a good base and we have a lot to play for with the series 1-1. We are playing the same team. With wickets in hand, we are a dangerous team. Very motivated from the rugby game. Happy to see my school-mate score there.
</p>
<p>
<strong>MS Dhoni</strong>: It looks a good surface. We were also looking to bat. But when we bowl, the spinners won't have dew. We have made one change with <b>Mishra coming in for Umesh</b>. Spinners have been our strength but fast bowlers haven't got their full quota.
</p>
<p>
So, India are playing three spinners to add to Raina's part-time offspin.
</p>
<p>
Marin Jose: "Gurkeerath should have chosen.." -- Well, Dhoni has said that he has to wait for his turn
</p>
<p>
Krish: "De Kock will be happy to bat on a belter like this one. He would love if the ball comes nicely on."
</p>
<p>
Kamal: "Both matches were pure thrillers. Expecting the same today even if it is a high-scoring pitch."
</p>
<p>
Ahsan Butt: "SA choose to bat first, <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/zimbabwe-v-afghanistan-2015-16/engine/match/924629.html" target="_blank">Afghanistan</a> choose to bat first. Batting Sunday in store, bring it ON."
</p>
<p>
<strong>12:50pm</strong>: This is such a terrific pitch to bat on and the outfield is magnificent, says the pitch report. Toss in ten minutes.
</p>
<p>
<strong>12:35pm</strong>: Hardik Patel, the young leader of a new movement demanding quotas for the Patidari community has <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/929645.html" target="_blank">threatened </a>to block the teams' way to send out a political message. And the security has been tightened everywhere on the town and en route to the stadium, says Rachna Shetty. The teams have not had trouble reaching the ground. They are now warming up.
</p>
<p>
venkat: "Its time for Virat and Raina to come to the party and this will give Dhoni licence. to play his free shots." -- And <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/video_audio/929601.html" target="_blank">Ajit Agarkar</a> has also identified that the form of Kohli and Raina is a big concern for the hosts
</p>
<p>
Mohit: "Strong Reply by Indian Captain in last game. Good to see the bowlers and fielders back Dhoni up in the last game."
</p>
<p>
yasir: "@Ashish ..Like in Spiderman " with great power come great responsibility'" same here.. "With captaincy and especially Indian captaincy comes pressure."
</p>
<p>
yasir: "Who is the commentator for this match, his name is not appearing on site, Alan Andrew, muthu ...????" -- I, Muthu Jr, and Nikhil Kalro will take you through the thrills and spills today.
</p>
<p>
Ashish: "I don't understand why <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/928935.html" target="_blank">Dhoni</a> always faces criticism if he fails to finish the game. His average for the last 10 games is far better than Virat Kohli." -- Because the Indian captain is always under pressure and India has demanding press corps.
</p>
<p>
"South Africa would have anticipated this. They knew that the bubble would burst," writes Firdose Moonda in the <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/929775.html" target="_blank">preview</a>. Meanwhile, Faf du Plessis has said that the <a href="http://www.espncricinfo.com/india-v-south-africa-2015-16/content/story/929901.html" target="_blank">Indore revival has given India a sniff.</a>
</p>
<p>
<strong>12:30pm</strong>: MS Dhoni came under fire for not finishing off the first ODI. He has been under fire for sometime for his minimal returns with the bat. However, he stepped up in Indore, producing a doughty 92 and then calmly leading India to parity. The series is nicely set up at 1-1. Good afternoon and welcome to ESPNcricinfo's ball-by-ball coverage of the third ODI.

<p class="commsText">
<b>5:11pm</b>: South Africa looked set for a 300-plus total during the 118-run partnership between QdK and Faf. However, the bowlers pulled things back admirably to keep the visitors to 270. Harbhajan broke a strong opening partnership, showed good control, and applied the brakes before Mishra and Axar pitched in. QdK struck his fourth century in seven innings against India but struggled to cope with the sweltering heat and eventually fell for 103. The two pacers also complemented the spinners, giving away only 60 runs in the last ten overs. Over to Nikhil Kalro for the chase.
</p>
<p class="commsText">
Aditya: "All 3 first innings finishing with a Six. We know the result of first 2. Just saying.."
</p>
<p class="commsText">
<b>Faf du Plessis</b>: It is important for the guys to extend the partnership. The spinners bowled well and squeezed it. There was just no breeze and it was like oven-like conditions bur our keeper needs some help.
</p>
